SEARCH IN ROTATED SORTED ARRAY II (WITH DUPLICATES)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Array nums is sorted in non-decreasing order but may contain duplicates.

Before calling the function, the array may be rotated at some pivot.

Example:

Original:
[0,1,2,4,4,4,5,6,6,7]

After rotation:
[4,5,6,6,7,0,1,2,4,4]


Goal:
Return true if target exists in nums, otherwise false.



Example 1:

Input:
nums = [2,5,6,0,0,1,2]
target = 0

Output:
true


Example 2:

Input:
nums = [2,5,6,0,0,1,2]
target = 3

Output:
false



Constraints:

1 <= nums.length <= 5000  
-10^4 <= nums[i] <= 10^4  
nums is rotated  
-10^4 <= target <= 10^4



Follow-up:

Because duplicates exist, worst-case time complexity may degrade to **O(n)**.

Example case causing degradation:
[1,1,1,1,1,1,1]

Binary search cannot determine which half is sorted.



────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MODIFIED BINARY SEARCH WITH DUPLICATES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

class Solution {
public:
    bool search(vector<int>& nums, int target) 
    {
        int str = 0;
        int end = nums.size() - 1;

        while(str <= end)
        {
            int mid = str + (end - str) / 2;

            if(nums[mid] == target)
            {
                return true;
            }

            if(nums[str] == nums[mid] && nums[mid] == nums[end])
            {
                str++;
                end--;
                continue;
            }

            if(nums[str] <= nums[mid])        // left half sorted
            {
                if(nums[str] <= target && target <= nums[mid])
                {
                    end = mid - 1;
                }
                else
                {
                    str = mid + 1;
                }
            }
            else                               // right half sorted
            {
                if(nums[mid] <= target && target <= nums[end])
                {
                    str = mid + 1;
                }
                else
                {
                    end = mid - 1;
                }
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
};
